1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bf4 O-O 6. e3 b6 7. Bd3 c5 8. cxd5
Nxd5 9. Nxd5 exd5 10. O-O c4 {Strictly speaking, this is not forced. But first
of all, it is useful to investigate this structure, which can arise in many
other situations. White needs to undertake something active as otherwise the
black pawns' advance would cause him problems.} ({Secondly, after} 10... Nc6 {
White can try} 11. Bb5 Bb7 12. b3 {Stopping ...c5-c4, White is now ready to
meet ...a7-a6 with Bd3/e2 after having forced the enemy bishop to occupy a
sub-optimal square. Fier,A (2603)-Grachev,B (2693) Basel 2012 (1/2-1/2, 27)})
11. Bc2 Nc6 {As we will see, it is best to delay the bishop's development.} 12.
Ne5 ({The point is that after} 12. b3 {Black has} Ba6 13. bxc4 Bxc4 {with
active queenside play.} 14. Bd3 Na5 (14... Nb4 $5 15. Bxc4 dxc4 16. a3 Nd3 17.
Bg3 b5 $15) 15. Ne5 (15. Qc2 Bxd3 16. Qxd3 Bd6 17. Be5 f6 18. Bxd6 Qxd6 19.
Rfc1 Rfc8 20. Qf5 Rxc1+ 21. Rxc1 g6 22. Qc2 Nc4 23. e4 b5 $11 {Banikas,H (2571)
-Sandalakis,A (2341) Paleochora 2008 (1/2-1/2, 41)}) 15... Bxd3 16. Nxd3 Rc8
17. Qa4 Rc3 18. Qb5 Qe8 19. Qxe8 Rxe8 20. Rfd1 Ba3 $15 {Pilaj,H (2389)-Stanec,
N (2538) Graz 2008 (0-1, 31)}) 12... Nxe5 13. Bxe5 f6 ({Another possible move
order is} 13... Be6 14. Qh5 g6 ({If Black does not want a draw he should
consider} 14... f5 $5 {Even though he usually does this after ...f7-f6, Lg3,
the extra tempo does not offer White that much activity.}) 15. Qh6 f6 16. Bxg6
hxg6 17. Qxg6+ Kh8 18. Qh6+ Kg8 {1/2-1/2 Malakhatko,V (2526)-Bellia,F (2425)
Gallipoli 2012}) 14. Bf4 (14. Qh5 g6 $11) 14... f5 (14... Be6 15. Qh5 f5 16.
Be5 b5 17. f4 g6 18. Qf3 Qd7 19. h3 a5 20. Kh1 a4 21. Rg1 b4 22. g4 Rad8 $15 {
Black's position is preferable as things are stable on the kingside, while on
the queenside his majority could become dangerous at any time, Rapport,R (2523)
-Horvath,C (2529) Hungary 2010 (1-0, 41)}) 15. Be5 Be6 16. f4 Qd7 17. h3 Bf6
18. Kh2 Rad8 19. Qe1 a5 20. a3 Ra8 21. Rd1 b5 22. Rg1 g6 23. Rd2 b4 $15 {
Vitiugov,N (2709)-Babula,V (2536) Czechia 2010 (1/2-1/2, 36) With a similar
evaluation as above.} *

