{7.Qb3 is the critical test for our setup with 5...Nf6. Do you remember how
Black should react?} 7... Nc6 $1 {A developing move, sacrificing the pawn on
b7 for the initiative.} 8. Qxb7 {critical test for Black's reply} Nb4 $1 {
Apart from ...Nc2+, Black also has some hopes to trap the queen, or at least
to reach a draw by perpetually attacking it} 9. Bb5+ Kf8 10. Kd2 Ne4+ $1 {
[%emt 0:00:13] With a double-edged position with mutual chances. For more
information check again chapter} *

